# Targets chezmoi should remove from the destination on every apply.
#
# Removing a file from the source tree does NOT delete its deployed target
# (chezmoi "forgets" it, leaving an orphan). These entries clean up orphans from
# the plan-mode migration:
#
#   - plan-mode-default.ts: the previous plan-mode approach (injected a synthetic
#     `/plan` user message at session_start). Replaced by the owned
#     extensions/plan-mode/ extension. It is a top-level .ts, so pi auto-loads
#     it — it MUST be removed or the old hack runs alongside the new extension.
#   - plan-mode/utils.ts: leftover from the old upstream-example external (now
#     replaced by owned source files in the same directory).
.pi/agent/extensions/plan-mode-default.ts
.pi/agent/extensions/plan-mode/utils.ts
# Orphans from the subagent-prompt migration: workflow prompts now render only
# to .pi/agent/prompts/. These exact legacy files were previously managed under
# the extension; list them individually rather than exact-syncing any broader
# .pi directory.
.pi/agent/extensions/subagent/prompts/implement-and-review.md
.pi/agent/extensions/subagent/prompts/implement.md
.pi/agent/extensions/subagent/prompts/scout-and-plan.md

# Orphans from the secrets-to-mise migration: per-secret files formerly
# rendered from exact_private_dot_secrets/, plus the shell loader scripts that
# sourced them (load-secrets.sh / load-secrets.ps1 were the sole contents of
# their dirs). Secrets now live in ~/.config/mise/conf.d/secrets.toml and are
# delivered via mise env.
.secrets
.config/sh
.config/powershell
